<H1>&nbsp;</H1>
<H1><FONT color=mediumblue>LSI (Latent Semantic Indexing) </FONT></H1>
</CENTER>

<UL><UL><UL><UL><UL><UL><UL>
       <LI><FONT size=5>LSI enables to find relevant information when it shares no words with their queries.</FONT></LI>
       <BR><BR>
       <LI><FONT size=5>LSI considers transcripts that have words in common that are semantically close.</FONT></LI>
       <BR><BR>
       <LI><FONT size=5>LSI does not require an exact match to return useful results.</FONT></LI>
       <BR><BR>
       <LI><FONT size=5>Same example, search on <FONT color=red>“Chronobot”</FONT> will return statements containing 	about <FONT color=red> “time-machine”, “virtual-classroom”,”DrChang”, ”Nocture”</FONT> </FONT></LI>
</UL></UL></UL></UL></UL></UL></UL>

